{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/preserving-the-results-of-a-throwing-expression"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/preserving-the-results-of-a-throwing-expression"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Preserving the Results of a Throwing Expression"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/init(catching:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Converting-a-Throwing-Expression-to-a-Result","title":"Converting a Throwing Expression to a Result"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/swift-standard-library","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/numbers-and-basic-values","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Call the initializer that wraps a throwing expression when you need to serialize"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or memoize the result."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes you need to preserve the entire result of a function call or other expression"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that can either throw or return a value. For example, you may need to serialize the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"result or pass it as a value to another part of your app that handles the result"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data. Use the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result"},{"type":"text","text":" type in these scenarios to capture the result of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"potentially failing operation."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Identify-a-Throwing-Expression-to-Preserve","text":"Identify a Throwing Expression to Preserve"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically, you use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"do-catch"},{"type":"text","text":" statements to handle throwing expressions immediately,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but sometimes you need to store the whole result of the operation for later processing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"during tasks like analyzing a batch of calls. The following example introduces an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API that generates random numbers, but that fails approximately half of the time."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["enum EntropyError: Error {","    case entropyDepleted","}","","struct UnreliableRandomGenerator {","    func random() throws -> Int {","        if Bool.random() {","            return Int.random(in: 1...100)","        } else {","            throw EntropyError.entropyDepleted","        }","    }","}"]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Convert-the-Throwing-Expression-to-a-Result","text":"Convert the Throwing Expression to a Result"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You preserve the return value or thrown error from a throwing expression using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result"},{"type":"text","text":" enumeration’s "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/init(catching:)"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer. Invoke"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the throwing expression inside the closure you pass to the initializer:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let singleSample = Result { try UnreliableRandomGenerator().random() }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In most scenarios, you use the preserved result as part of broader functionality"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in your code. For example, you may run a series of randomness tests and compute the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"statistical average of both a range of numbers returned from a random number generator,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as well as the failure rate of calling the API. In these cases, you need to store"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the whole result rather than just the success value or that the API call failed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example uses the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/init(catching:)"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"broader context of saving a series of calls for later statistical analysis:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct RandomnessMonitor {","    let randomnessSource: UnreliableRandomGenerator","    var results: [Result<Int, Error>] = []","","    init(generator: UnreliableRandomGenerator) {","        randomnessSource = generator","    }","","    mutating func sample() {","        let sample = Result { try randomnessSource.random() }","        results.append(sample)","    }","","    func summary() -> (Double, Double) {","        let totals = results.reduce((sum: 0, count: 0)) { total, sample in","            switch sample {","            case .success(let number):","                return (total.sum + number, total.count)","            case .failure:","                return (total.sum, total.count + 1)","            }","        }","","        return (","            average: Double(totals.sum) \/ Double(results.count - totals.count),","            failureRate: Double(totals.count) \/ Double(results.count)","        )","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Running the analysis on a sufficiently large sample generates an average number near"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"50 and a failure rate near 50%:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["var monitor = RandomnessMonitor(generator: UnreliableRandomGenerator())","(0..<1000).forEach { _ in monitor.sample() }","let (average, failureRate) = monitor.summary()","print(\"Average value: \\(average), failure rate: \\(failureRate * 100.0)%.\")","\/\/ Prints values such as: \"Average value: 47.95, failure rate: 48.69%.\""]}]}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Result/init(catching:)":{"conformance":{"conformancePrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Conforms when"}],"availabilityPrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Available when"}],"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Failure"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a new result by evaluating a throwing closure, capturing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returned value as a success, or any thrown error as a failure."}],"title":"init(catching:)","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/result\/init(catching:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/init(catching:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"catching"},{"kind":"text","text":": () "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s6ResultOsRi_zrlE7Failureq_mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Failure"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s6ResultOsRi_zrlE7Successxmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Success"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/numbers-and-basic-values":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/numbers-and-basic-values","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/numbers-and-basic-values","abstract":[{"text":"Model data with numbers, Boolean values, and other fundamental types.","type":"text"}],"title":"Numbers and Basic Values"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/swift-standard-library":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Solve complex problems and write high-performance, readable code.","type":"text"}],"title":"Swift Standard Library","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/swift-standard-library","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/swift-standard-library","kind":"article"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swift","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Build apps using a powerful open language.","type":"text"}],"title":"Swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Result":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Result"}],"title":"Result","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Result"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result","type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A value that represents either a success or a failure, including an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"associated value in each case."}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/result"}}}